{:source ["plugins/rama-skill/skills/rama/SKILL.md" "plugins/rama-skill/skills/rama/references/external-depots.md" "plugins/rama-skill/skills/rama/references/patterns.md" "plugins/rama-skill/skills/rama/references/task-globals.md"], :question "# Rama Integration\n\nHow do you introduce Rama to an existing architecture that already uses lots of other tooling?\n\nWrite your answer to `implementations/qa-rama-integration/answer.md`.", :extracted-at "2026-03-30T18:14:13.727640Z", :claims ["ExternalDepot adapts an external partitioned log (e.g. Kafka, Kinesis, custom queue) into the Rama depot abstraction." "Topologies consume ExternalDepots identically to native depots — same source>, same start-from options, same retry semantics." "Kafka integration is provided via the rama-kafka artifact using the KafkaExternalDepot class." "ExternalDepot extends TaskGlobalObject, so implementations must provide prepareForTask and close methods." "ExternalDepot interface methods must return CompletableFuture (non-blocking contract); blocking calls stall the Rama worker thread." "Rama calls fetchFrom for streaming only when consuming topologies have available capacity, automatically throttling the external source (backpressure)." "getNumPartitions() is polled every ~30 seconds, allowing Rama to detect and begin consuming new partitions when the external source scales." "External depots are read-only from Rama's perspective — data is appended by the external system." "Foreign client APIs allow external application code to append to depots and read PStates via foreign-append!, foreign-select-one, foreign-select, and foreign-invoke-query." "Depot, PState, and query client handles should be created once via foreign-depot, foreign-pstate, and foreign-query and reused across calls." "foreign-append! with :ack on an owned stream depot guarantees PState visibility after return." "foreign-append! with :ack on a microbatch depot only confirms depot replication, not PState visibility." "TaskGlobals can hold external clients, caches, ML models, and connection pools as per-task non-durable resources." "TaskGlobalObjectWithTick enables periodic operations such as cache refresh, heartbeat, or metrics flush on a per-task basis." "For microbatch topologies writing to external systems, ops/current-microbatch-id should be used to version writes for exactly-once semantics." "Application code can interact with a running Rama cluster through foreign client handles for HTTP handlers, CLI tools, and background jobs." "The enrichment orchestrator pattern allows application code to fetch supporting data from Rama before processing a workflow step." "The response orchestrator pattern allows an API endpoint to gather data from Rama queries and PStates to build a response." "For graph/tree traversals, a point-read query should be exposed and BFS/DFS run in client code with repeated foreign-invoke-query calls." "Paths passed to foreign-select run on the source module's topology, so all functions used in paths must be present in the source module code on its classpath." "The foreign depot API provides foreign-depot-partition-info and foreign-depot-read for direct access to depot data from external code." "A module can declare only a depot with no topologies, allowing direct use of depot APIs from external tools." "TaskGlobals are serialized to each task; field types must be serializable (primitives, arrays, Strings) — types like AtomicInteger lack registered serializers." "In InProcessCluster testing, external depots work normally and can be backed with a global atom and a deftype implementing ExternalDepot." "The documentation reference for integrating Rama with other tools is https://redplanetlabs.com/docs/~/integrating.html." "completable-future> wraps an async external call within a topology; the topology suspends until the CompletableFuture delivers, then emits the result."]}
